Date: 0/0/1956
Source: Wool Away!
Author: BOWEN
Vol / Page: 157
Edition:
Quote: SHEEPO. The man who fills the catching pens and works sheep in the shed. Shearers give the call of `sheepo' when they have caught the last sheep in the catching pen, and to signify that the pen is empty.
