Author: MILLS
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote: The title of this book is the call of the shearer when his catching pen is empty, and it is inseparable from the shearing and crutching of sheep. <i>Ibid.</i> 27 Standing among the sheep were two men whose duty it was to fill the pens, the sheep-os Bill Ritchie and Link Campbell; there would be no insistent call of `Sheep-O!' this day.
